-- Clayton, Dubilier & Rice Names Ex-Bayer Chief Adviser
-- B y   S a u m y a   V a i s h a m p a y a n
-- 2012-10-01T13:06:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-01/clayton-dubilier-rice-names-ex-bayer-chief-adviser.html
Clayton, Dubilier & Rice LLC, the
buyout firm that this year agreed to acquire David’s Bridal Inc.
for $1.05 billion, named Manfred Schneider, the former chief
executive officer of  Bayer AG (BAYN) , as an adviser.  Schneider expanded Bayer’s research and development and
increased the German drugmaker’s presence in North America and
Asia when he ran the company from 1992 to 2002, Clayton,
Dubilier & Rice said today in a statement.  “He is an exceptional global industrial leader with a
track record of driving growth and innovation across three
continents,” Donald Gogel, CEO of Clayton, Dubilier & Rice,
said in the statement.  Schneider is also a member of supervisory boards of
industrial engineering company Linde AG and utility company RWE
AG.  To contact the reporter on this story:
